<p>SEO leads close at a 14.6% rate. Outbound leads close at 1.7%. That gap is not small. It is the difference between a marketing channel that drives revenue and one that burns budget.</p>
<p>Most businesses treat SEO for lead generation as an afterthought. They publish blog posts, chase rankings, and hope traffic converts. It rarely does. The problem is not SEO itself. The problem is SEO without a conversion strategy. Traffic without a path to leads is just a vanity metric.</p>
<p>Organic search costs roughly $31 per lead on average. Paid search costs $181 per lead (<a href="https://firstpagesage.com/reports/average-cost-per-lead-by-industry/">First Page Sage</a>). SEO delivers 748% ROI through thought leadership content. These numbers tell you where to invest. But the numbers only work when you combine ranking strategy with conversion optimization.</p>
<p>We have published 3,500+ blog posts across 70+ industries. The pattern is clear: companies that align their SEO strategy with their sales funnel generate 3 to 5 times more leads per 1,000 visitors than companies that optimize for traffic alone.</p>
