<h2>What Is SEO Lead Generation</h2>
<p>SEO lead generation is the practice of using organic search traffic to attract, engage, and convert visitors into qualified leads. It combines search engine optimization with conversion rate optimization to turn rankings into revenue.</p>
<p>There are 2 types:</p>
<p><strong>Direct lead generation</strong> targets transactional keywords where the searcher is ready to buy or inquire. Examples: "commercial plumber near me," "CRM software pricing," "SEO agency for law firms." These pages convert visitors into leads immediately through forms, phone calls, or chat.</p>
<p><strong>Indirect lead generation</strong> targets informational keywords where the searcher is researching. Examples: "how to fix a leaking pipe," "best practices for sales automation," "local SEO guide." These pages build trust and authority over time, moving readers into your funnel through CTAs, lead magnets, and email capture.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="SEO lead generation funnel from traffic to revenue" src="/images/blog/seo-lead-generation-funnel.webp" /></p>
<p>Both types work. The best SEO lead generation strategies use both in combination. Direct pages convert the ready buyers. Indirect pages capture the future buyers who are not ready yet.</p>
