<p>Start with bottom-of-funnel keywords. They generate leads faster. Then expand upward to build the pipeline. Use our <a href="/blog/keyword-research-for-blog-posts/">keyword research guide</a> to find the right terms for each stage.</p>
<h3>Target High-Intent Modifiers</h3>
<p>Add these modifiers to your seed keywords to find terms with buyer intent:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Pricing/cost modifiers:</strong> "pricing," "cost," "how much," "plans"</li>
<li><strong>Comparison modifiers:</strong> "vs," "compared to," "alternative to," "better than"</li>
<li><strong>Location modifiers:</strong> "near me," "[city] + [service]," "local"</li>
<li><strong>Action modifiers:</strong> "hire," "buy," "get quote," "free trial," "demo"</li>
<li><strong>Problem modifiers:</strong> "fix," "repair," "troubleshoot," "why is my"</li>
</ul>
<p>These modifiers signal commercial intent. Pages targeting these terms convert at 3 to 10 times the rate of generic informational keywords.</p>
<h3>Match Search Intent to Content Format</h3>
<p>Google rewards pages that match <a href="/blog/search-intent-guide/">search intent</a>. The wrong format for the right keyword kills conversions:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>"Best [X]" queries</strong> need ranked list posts with pros, cons, and pricing</li>
<li><strong>"How to [X]" queries</strong> need step-by-step guides with visuals</li>
<li><strong>"[X] near me" queries</strong> need location pages with contact info and reviews</li>
<li><strong>"[X] vs [Y]" queries</strong> need comparison tables with a clear verdict</li>
<li><strong>"[X] pricing" queries</strong> need transparent pricing pages with feature breakdowns</li>
</ul>
<p>Check the SERPs before creating any page. The format that ranks is the format Google has confirmed matches intent for that query.</p>
