<h3>Attribution Models</h3>
<p>SEO leads rarely come from a single touchpoint. A typical buyer journey looks like this:</p>
<ol>
<li>First visit from a blog post (awareness)</li>
<li>Return visit from a comparison page (consideration)</li>
<li>Direct visit to pricing page (decision)</li>
<li>Form submission (conversion)</li>
</ol>
<p>If you only track last-click attribution, step 4 gets the credit. The blog post that started the journey gets zero. Use <a href="/blog/measure-content-marketing-roi/">multi-touch attribution</a> to understand which content actually drives leads.</p>
<p>Google Analytics 4 uses data-driven attribution by default. This distributes credit across touchpoints based on modeled conversion paths. It is a better starting point than last-click, but review the data regularly to understand your actual buyer journey.</p>
